Owner / Maintained by
Prospera Architecture Group

Governing Authority
Prospera OS Governance Kernel

Purpose

This document defines an executable, governed, and auditable pipeline for
generating client-facing Documentation Governance Reports from machine-generated
documentation inventory artifacts.

The specification conforms to international engineering documentation standards
by providing explicit interfaces, execution matrices, control points, and
enforcement rules.

Scope

This pipeline governs:

Deterministic transformation of documentation inventory data

Automated execution within CI environments

Controlled exposure of governance results to clients

This pipeline explicitly excludes:

Documentation remediation

Content modification

Manual interpretation of inventory data

Input Artifacts
| Artifact Name                                                     | Description            | Authority |
| ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- | --------- |
| documentation-inventory-report.json                               | Inventory data source  | SSOT      |
| Inventory_JSON_to_Documentation_Governance_Report_Mapping_v1.0.md | Transformation rules   | Canonical |
| Documentation_Governance_Report_v1.0_Client.md                    | Client report template | Canonical |

Pipeline Execution Matrix
| Step ID | Step Name            | Input Artifacts       | Output Artifacts    | Failure Condition | Enforcement Action |
| ------- | -------------------- | --------------------- | ------------------- | ----------------- | ------------------ |
| P1      | Inventory Validation | Inventory JSON        | Validated inventory | Schema violation  | BLOCK              |
| P2      | Mapping Validation   | Mapping specification | Validated mapping   | Version mismatch  | BLOCK              |
| P3      | Metric Computation   | Validated inventory   | Computed metrics    | Undefined rule    | BLOCK              |
| P4      | Report Rendering     | Metrics, template     | Draft report        | Rendering error   | BLOCK              |
| P5      | Output Verification  | Draft report          | Final report        | Missing section   | BLOCK              |

All steps SHALL execute sequentially.
Parallel execution is PROHIBITED.

Control Points Definition
Control Point CP-01
| Attribute       | Value                               |
| --------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Name            | Inventory Schema Validation         |
| Trigger         | Before Step P1                      |
| Validation Rule | Required keys and structure present |
| Failure Action  | Immediate pipeline termination      |

Control Point CP-02
| Attribute       | Value                               |
| --------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Name            | Mapping Authority Validation        |
| Trigger         | Before Step P2                      |
| Validation Rule | Mapping version and authority match |
| Failure Action  | Immediate pipeline termination      |

Control Point CP-03
| Attribute       | Value                              |
| --------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Name            | Metric Determinism Validation      |
| Trigger         | After Step P3                      |
| Validation Rule | All metrics traceable to inventory |
| Failure Action  | Immediate pipeline termination     |

Control Point CP-04
| Attribute       | Value                          |
| --------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Name            | Client Exposure Validation     |
| Trigger         | Before Step P5                 |
| Validation Rule | No internal data exposed       |
| Failure Action  | Immediate pipeline termination |

Execution Boundary Matrix
| Activity              | Responsible Executor | Automation Permitted |
| --------------------- | -------------------- | -------------------- |
| Inventory Scanning    | CI System            | Yes                  |
| Metric Computation    | Pipeline Engine      | Yes                  |
| Mapping Modification  | Governance Authority | No                   |
| Report Generation     | CI System            | Yes                  |
| Client Interpretation | Human Consultant     | No                   |
| Remediation Execution | Separate Workflow    | No                   |

Codex operates strictly as a non-authoritative Engineering Worker.

Enforcement Rules

Inventory artifacts SHALL be treated as read-only

Undocumented transformation logic is PROHIBITED

Pipeline SHALL fail fast on any governance violation

Successful executions SHALL be reproducible

Auditability Requirements

All reported values SHALL be derivable from inventory JSON

Control point results SHALL be recorded per execution

Execution logs SHALL be retained according to CI policy

Change Control
| Change Type                 | Requirement                  |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Execution logic change      | Minor version increment      |
| Governance rule change      | Governance approval required |
| Client report format change | Major version increment      |

End of Document
